					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex written in square Ashkenazi script, punctuated and accentuated.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>508 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>476</height>
										<width>368</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>508 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves and a parchment flyleaf at the end). </p>
									<p>Original Hebrew foliation not visible. Quires are marked by catchwords at the end, the mark בי being written in the upper right-hand corner at the beginning of the quires. </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>65 quires, mostly of 8 leaves each, marked by catchwords at the end. Several quires are missing after folio 436 (parts of Job, Proverbs and all the Five Scrolls). </p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="3" ruledLines="31" writtenLines="30">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Pricking and ruling visible. Ruled with a pencil (both main text and masoretic notes). </p>
									<p>Leviticus, Joshua, Kings and Isaiah begin a new leaf, and Psalms open a new page. </p>
									<p>Beginning of a weekly section marked by the word סדר in the margin. The sign פפ stands between the sections. </p>
									<p>Beginning and end of the Torah lessons for feasts and fasts marked in red (folio 14r,  45v, 46v). </p>
									<p>Masorah magna is written in two lines in the upper margin and in three lines in the lower margin. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="3">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square script for the main text and semi-cursive for masorah. One folio with masoretic lists written with a Greek hand (Syracuse).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
